The paper discusses a methodology for evaluating word representations in natural language processing, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The methodology involves identifying subspaces necessary to satisfy certain criteria, which suggests a focus on machine learning and linear algebra techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also compares different models, which could fall under the categories of neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the models involve image processing.
